The paper is about improving code completion using language models, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The paper also discusses the use of LSTM models and the handling of unseen words, which are common topics in natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed Hierarchical Language Model (HLM) also involves the use of neural networks, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the syntax tree structure of code, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL).
